==English==

===Etymology===
From the Hebrew word [[אבדון]] (''abdon'', meaning ''servant''). [[cf|Cf]] the Arabic {{ARchar|عبد}} (''abd'') in [[Abdullah]], also meaning ''servant''.

===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun}}
#{{Judaism}} the tenth [[judge]] of Israel in Judges 12.13-15: [[w:Abdon (Judges)|w:Abdon]].
#{{given name|male|from Hebrew|}} A [[Hebrew]] male [[given name]].

